social_posts.post_text:
Hello! 
It’s been a while since I’ve posted anything and figured it was time to update this page with what’s going on in my life right now. I announced it in my stories last week but in case you missed it, I am currently pregnant with Banks baby #4. 🎉👶🏼

So YES I am still alive and I have just been lying around trying to grow a baby and fight the mental and physical demons that make doing normal tasks like brushing my teeth or going to the grocery store seem impossible. The nausea is relentless and exhausting. I don’t know when I will be back to normal (both with my family life and with my business life) and that’s hard for me. I want to say I have been so humbled these last several weeks in learning to accept help when it has been offered. I’ve been brought to tears almost daily by friends, neighbors, and family who have come to bring food, offer childcare, or help clean my ever-declining house. My husband and children have been so gracious towards me and my situation and I wish I didn’t feel so guilty for not being as energetic and available for them as I typically am when not pregnant. 
Anyway, I want to be transparent that while I am truly thrilled to be pregnant, I also am struggling really badly with not feeling well. 

I can’t wait to get back to feeling normal and back to working on cookies for your events. Hopefully it will be very soon!!! I appreciate everyone who has reached out to check on me and also want to say thanks for all of the congratulations for our baby announcement. I have the best people in my life 🥰🥰🥰

It’s been a while since my last cookie post and I remembered I never shared these cookies I made for @carrieunderwood when she came to Utah last year! 

I fell in love with her when she was on American Idol and I hear the concert was incredible! Hope she enjoyed these cookies after her show! 

I share here how I used the @intricutedibles embossed parchment squares to create a background texture on a few of the cookies. This was my first time adding edible glitter underneath the paper and I think it turned so beautifully!! 

Floral champagne bottle from @cookiecuttersbynori 

#concertcookies #carrieunderwood #carrieunderwoodfans #denimandrhinestonestour #thecookiebank #cookiereels

Edible Opal cookies… can you even?! 🤩 I loved getting to stretch my creative brain and create this Opal themed set of cookies for the World Cookie Summit last week. If you missed it, no worries because the class with step-by-step instructions on all of these designs is still available now for purchase in the Cookie Library at the link in my profile. 

October’s traditional birth stone is the Opal and that’s my birth month so it was extra fun to think of ways to make this gorgeous stone in cookie form. I feel like there are so many fun applications that you could use this technique in. If you end up trying this, I would love to see how you use these techniques so please tag me so I can share!!!

Justine Banks, the owner of @thecookiebank turned her post-partum cookie decorating hobby into a business starting in 2015. Her business really took off when she was asked by the local sports Arena in Salt Lake City, Utah to create custom curated cookie sets for all the celebrities who come to perform there. Because of this opportunity, Justine has had the privilege of making personalized sets of cookies for artists such as P!nk, Justin Bieber, Sir Elton John, The Backstreet Boys, Adam Sandler, Ariana Grande, Post Malone, and many more. 
•
Justine made her TV debut in 2021 competing on Food Network’s Christmas Cookie Challenge, and was invited back in 2022 to compete on a brand new Food Network show, Halloween Cookie Challenge. This time she claimed the $10,000 prize and title of “Halloween Cookie Champion.”
•
Outside of cookies, Justine is a wife and the proud mother of three sons and one daughter. She loves to fill her free time by either being physically active at the gym, or by binging a new netflix show and eating Cake Batter ice cream with fatty chunks of cookie dough. It’s all about balance, right?

Come and join Justine with @thecookiebank at the @flourisheventsandretreats retreat in Sept 2024. You will learn some jaw-dropping (pun intended) techniques that helped her win Food Network’s Halloween Cookie Challenge. In this gruesome, hands-on class, students will learn to create six hyper-realistic, gross-looking but delicious tasting cookies. The techniques students will learn in this class include freehand and stenciled airbrushing, hand painting for details and shading, sculpting with fondant and with thick royal icing, and methods for creating various “wet-looking” details.  While this class is intended for Intermediate and Advanced level decorators, all students who have an interest in learning these techniques are welcome. All tools and supplies will be provided. Students will take home their class creations and many of the hand tools/materials used in the class.

@intricutedibles is where it’s at for all your textured cookie needs. Such a simple technique but it adds a designer element to your cookies. They have so many new holiday textures to choose from too! I can’t wait to show you a few of them and how I plan to use them this season. Go check them out!

The hidden talents we found in this class were amazing. Watch the video to see what I mean.  Can you believe that it was his first time decorating with royal icing? Me neither. 😉Need an idea for your holiday party? Call your cookie girl! Thanks for having me @aspenridgemanagement  and especially to you @hilaryadavis for being such a supportive and wonderful neighbor and friend.

I might have made fewer cookies this year but they were some of my favorites to date!! Love that this is my job and I love that you all trust me to add something special and delicious to your events. Happy New Year!!
